<item>
            <title>[LU-19790] Nodemap multiple filesets: do not allow alternating rw/ro flags on fileset subdir hierarchy</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19790</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When creating multiple filesets, it is possible to define alternating rw/ro flags within the same directory hierarchy:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;1. /t1
2. /t1/ro_subdir (ro)
3. /t1/ro_subdir/rw_subdir
4. /t1/ro_subdir/rw_subdir/ro_subdir2 (ro) &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While this provides flexibility when setting multiple filesets, it also risks accidentally making read-only directories read-write. In this case, when 3 is mounted, the subdir from 4 can be accessed through a read-write mountpoint. Therefore, the creation of filesets 3 and 4 should not be possible.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
